web_analytics.overview.titles.web_vitals: INP measures a page's overall responsiveness to user interactions by observing the latency of all click, tap, and keyboard interactions.
LCP measures the render time of the largest image or text block visible within the viewport.
CLS measures the largest burst of layout shift scores for every unexpected shift that occurs during the lifespan of a page.
TTFB measures the time between when a request is first made and when the first byte of a response begins to arrive.
